---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getMarket } from '../lib/market.ts';
const market = getMarket(Astro.url.hostname);
const brandName = market.brandName || 'TrainedBy';
const domain = market.domain;
const effectiveDate = 'January 1, 2025';
---

<Base
  title={`Cookie Policy — ${brandName}`}
  description={`Cookie Policy for ${brandName}. Learn how we use cookies and how to manage your preferences.`}
>
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  :root {
    --brand: #FF5C00;
    --bg: #fafaf8;
    --text: #1a1411;
    --text-2: rgba(26,20,17,0.55);
    --border: rgba(26,20,17,0.1);
    --max: 760px;
  }
  body { background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); font-family: 'Manrope', system-ui, sans-serif; line-height: 1.7; }
  .wrap { max-width: var(--max); margin: 0 auto; padding: 80px 24px 120px; }
  .back { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; color: var(--brand); text-decoration: none; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  h1 { font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .meta { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 48px; }
  h2 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin: 40px 0 12px; }
  p { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text); }
  ul { margin: 12px 0 16px 20px; }
  li { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  a { color: var(--brand); }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 16px 0 24px; font-size: 14px; }
  th { text-align: left; padding: 10px 12px; background: rgba(26,20,17,0.05); font-weight: 700; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  td { padding: 10px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); vertical-align: top; }
  nav { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 32px 24px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; max-width: var(--max); margin: 0 auto; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .nav-logo { font-family: 'Manrope', system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 900; font-size: 18px; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; }
  .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 20px; }
  .nav-links a { color: var(--text-2); text-decoration: none; font-size: 13px; }
  .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--text); }
</style>

<div class="wrap">
  <a href="/landing" class="back">← {brandName}</a>

  <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate} · Last updated: {effectiveDate}</p>

  <p>This Cookie Policy explains how {brandName} ("we", "us", or "our") uses cookies and similar tracking technologies when you visit {domain}. By continuing to use our Service, you consent to our use of cookies as described in this policy.</p>

  <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
  <p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently, as well as to provide information to website owners. Cookies can be "persistent" (they remain on your device until deleted) or "session" cookies (they are deleted when you close your browser).</p>

  <h2>2. Cookies We Use</h2>
  <p>We use the following categories of cookies:</p>

  <h2>2.1 Strictly Necessary Cookies</h2>
  <p>These cookies are essential for the Service to function and cannot be disabled. They are usually set in response to actions you take, such as logging in or filling in forms.</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
    <tr><td>sb-auth-token</td><td>Supabase authentication session token</td><td>Session</td></tr>
    <tr><td>sb-refresh-token</td><td>Supabase session refresh token</td><td>30 days</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>2.2 Functional Cookies</h2>
  <p>These cookies enable enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third-party providers.</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
    <tr><td>tb-market</td><td>Remembers your market/region preference</td><td>1 year</td></tr>
    <tr><td>tb-theme</td><td>Stores your display preference</td><td>1 year</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>2.3 Analytics Cookies</h2>
  <p>These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with the Service so we can improve it. The information collected is aggregated and anonymous.</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Provider</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
    <tr><td>_session_id</td><td>{brandName}</td><td>Tracks anonymous funnel events to improve onboarding</td><td>Session</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
  <p>Some of our pages may include content from third-party services that may set their own cookies. These third parties include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — Payment processing. See <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe's privacy policy</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — Font delivery (no tracking cookies set).</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not control third-party cookies. Please refer to each third party's privacy and cookie policy for more information.</p>

  <h2>4. How to Manage Cookies</h2>
  <p>Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can typically:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>View the cookies stored on your device</li>
    <li>Block all cookies or cookies from specific websites</li>
    <li>Delete cookies stored on your device</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of the Service. For example, disabling authentication cookies will prevent you from logging in.</p>
  <p>For guidance on how to manage cookies in popular browsers:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Chrome</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple Safari</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Do Not Track</h2>
  <p>Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" (DNT) feature that signals to websites that you do not want your browsing activity tracked. Our Service does not currently respond to DNT signals, but we do not sell your personal data to third parties.</p>

  <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "last updated" date at the top.</p>

  <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies, please contact us at:</p>
  <p>
    <strong>{brandName}</strong><br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:legal@{domain}">legal@{domain}</a><br />
    Website: <a href="https://{domain}">https://{domain}</a>
  </p>
</div>

<nav>
  <a href="/landing" class="nav-logo">{brandName}</a>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
    <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
    <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookies</a>
  </div>
</nav>
</Base>
